description.narrative: By 2020, 7,200 children aged 3-5 years in the 5 target districts, especially in remote areas, benefit from quality early learning programmes., which contributes to Early Childhood Development, Early Learning, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Equitable Access To Quality Education (Covid), Learning And Child-Friendly Schools, Learning Outcomes. description.narrative: The average enrollment per year in community preschools for the past four years is 3,500 children (total: 12,000), surpassing the output target of 7,200 children. UNICEF-supported community preschools cater to nearly half (46 %) of preschool-going children in the two target Municipalities. This represents about 3 % of all children in preschools in Timor-Leste. The community-based preschools provide a tried and tested, cost-effective model to enhance preschool access without compromising on quality of learning; using a partnership approach that involves communities, civil society, and government. This model will complement conventional preschools to achieve the ambitious targets set for early learning. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:05/02/2020
